text: Kevin Hart used to be a favorite of mine. What a cash grab. Comedians who make this much money should make you cry laughing on the worst day of your life. There are numerous comedians out there who are that funny, Kevin just ain't one of them anymore. Used to be. Just lost touch. Second you become that mainstream your edge becomes super dull. Exactly what happened here. Not hating on Kevin, not saying he doesn't deserve his money, he has fans that pay to see him. Good for him. Any hardcore comedy buff knows there's nothing new to see here. Rather listen to Pryor, Murphy, Wright, Carlin, Hicks, Chappelle, Old Kat, Jeffries, Jeselnik, Gervais, Segura, Birbiglia, Burr.... Heck, even Chris Porter. The short jokes are way too old. It seems more like group polarization than something that's tear-inducingly funny. I already know what to expect form Kevin Hart standup. He fails to keep it fresh. Still a fan of older Hart though. Just never broke through with fresh enough material for me. Feels recycled.

I know that he made history - selling out a football stadium - and is proud of that fact. His jokes were overly predictable, and not at all funny in some cases.
